ASABA – Delta State Governor, Dr Ifeanyi Okowa on Monday warned newly elected lo­cal government chairmen against abandoning proj­ects started by their prede­cessors. Speaking in Asaba during the swearing-in of the elect­ed 25 local government chairmen across the state, Okowa said the landslide victory of the Peoples Dem­ocratic Party ( PDP) in the March 6 local government elections demonstrated the supremacy of the party in the state. He urged the new chair­men to hit the ground run­ning by formulating policies that will impact the well-be­ing of their constituents. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! ” Do not abandon projects started by your predeces­sors. Instead, you can fine-tune such projects to suit your taste. “You should come up with ways to improve Internally Generated Revenue ( IGR) without overburdening your people,” he asserted. Equities Market Begins Week Positive, Up 0.17% Buhari’s APC Is Visionless, Can’t Think, Says Sule Lamido While emphasizing the need for security as a means of propagating development, Okowa mandated them to make urgent decisions to solve the recent inter-com­munal crisis in areas affect­ing their constituency.